---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - TribleTunes"
  description="TribleTunes Privacy Policy - Learn how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information on our platform."
  keywords="privacy policy, data protection, TribleTunes privacy, user information, user rights"
>
  <style slot="head">
    /* INFO CARD */
    .info-card {
      background: var(--bg-card);
      border: 2px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: clamp(10px, 2vw, 15px);
      padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 30px);
      margin: clamp(20px, 3vh, 30px) 0;
      box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
      text-align: left;
    }

    .info-card h3 {
      font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.3rem);
      color: var(--accent-color);
      margin-bottom: clamp(12px, 2vh, 15px);
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
    }

    .info-card h3 ion-icon {
      font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.5rem);
    }

    .info-card p,
    .info-card ul {
      font-size: clamp(0.9rem, 2vw, 1rem);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: clamp(10px, 2vh, 15px);
    }

    .info-card ul {
      padding-left: clamp(20px, 4vw, 30px);
    }

    .info-card li {
      margin-bottom: clamp(8px, 1.5vh, 10px);
    }

    /* FANCY HR LINES */
    hr.fancy-line {
      border: 0;
      height: clamp(2px, 0.3vh, 3px);
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--accent-color), transparent);
      margin: clamp(30px, 5vh, 50px) auto;
      border-radius: 5px;
      max-width: min(600px, 80%);
      opacity: 0.6;
    }
  </style>

  <!-- PRIVACY POLICY SECTION -->
  <section id="privacy-policy">
    <h2 class="section-title">Privacy Policy</h2>
    <h3 class="section-subtitle">Your Privacy Matters to Us</h3>

    <p class="section-text">
      At TribleTunes, accessible from <a href="https://tribletunes.com">tribletunes.com</a>, one of our main priorities
      is the privacy of our visitors and contributors. This Privacy Policy document contains types of information that
      are collected and recorded by TribleTunes and how we use it.
    </p>

    <hr class="fancy-line">

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="information-circle-outline"></ion-icon> Information We Collect</h3>
      <p>
        We may collect personal information such as your name, email address, and any other details you voluntarily
        provide when you contact us, submit music, or subscribe to updates. We also collect basic analytics data such
        as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Device information</li>
        <li>Pages visited and time spent</li>
        <li>Referring website addresses</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This data helps us improve user experience and optimize our platform.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="apps-outline"></ion-icon> How We Use Your Information</h3>
      <p>We use collected information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to your messages or inquiries</li>
        <li>Feature your submissions and music content (if applicable)</li>
        <li>Improve site performance and user experience</li>
        <li>Send updates related to TribleTunes (only if you opt-in)</li>
        <li>Analyze website traffic and user behavior</li>
        <li>Prevent fraud and ensure platform security</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="git-network-outline"></ion-icon> Cookies</h3>
      <p>
        Like many other websites, TribleTunes uses 'cookies' to store information such as visitors' preferences and
        pages visited. This information helps us customize web content for a better user experience.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can choose to disable cookies through your browser settings. However, this may affect your ability to use
        certain features of our website.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="link-outline"></ion-icon> Third-Party Links</h3>
      <p>
        Our website may contain links to external platforms such as YouTube, Spotify, SoundCloud, or artist pages. These
        sites are not operated by TribleTunes, and we are not responsible for their content or privacy policies.
      </p>
      <p>
        We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit. We have no control over and assume
        no responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third-party sites or services.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="shield-checkmark-outline"></ion-icon> Data Security</h3>
      <p>
        We take reasonable precautions to protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the
        Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect
        your personal data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="people-outline"></ion-icon> Children's Privacy</h3>
      <p>
        TribleTunes does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under the age of 13. If
        you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us
        immediately.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="checkmark-circle-outline"></ion-icon> Consent</h3>
      <p>
        By using our website, you hereby consent to our Privacy Policy and agree to its terms. If you do not agree with
        this policy, please do not use our website.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="refresh-outline"></ion-icon> Changes to This Policy</h3>
      <p>
        We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy
        Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date below.
      </p>
      <p>
        You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are
        effective when they are posted on this page.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-card">
      <h3><ion-icon name="mail-outline"></ion-icon> Contact Us</h3>
      <p>
        For questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@tribletunes.com">contact@tribletunes.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="section-text" style="text-align: center; margin-top: 30px;">
      <strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 2025
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
